<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-496-807  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 496 807.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Oct 8 1990 n611 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sematech taps Spencer as new chief. (William J. Spencer)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Xerox Corp executive William J. Spencer has been named presidentand CEO of Sematech, replacing Robert Noyce, who died in Jun 1990.andO;The 60-year-old Spencer has a background as both a manager and atechnologist and most recently served as vice president and seniortechnical officer at Xerox.andP;  The selection of Spencer is theculmination of a search that began before the death of Noyce,triggered by his announcement to the board that he wanted to beable to step down from the position by Oct 1990.andP;  His successoradmits to having little exact knowledge of Sematech, havinggathered much of what knowledge he does have through visits withNoyce.andP;  Daily operations will continue to be overseen by chiefoperating officer Turner Hasty, leaving Spencer free toconcentrate on formulating strategy, working with the consortium'sboard, and pursuing the consortium's interests in Washington.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ConsortiaSemiconductor IndustryExecutiveNew AppointmentSemiconductor Manufacturing Technology Institute.andO;Person:    Spencer, William J. (selection and appointment).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>